    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I encountered the same issue on my Raspberry Pi. To resolve it, I added the following parameters to the <code>/boot/cmdline.txt</code> file: <code>cgroup_enable=cpuset cgroup_enable=memory cgroup_memory=1</code>.</p>\n<p>Consider @<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/10967630/sayantanrc\" title=\"949 reputation\">SayantanRC</a>s comment:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Please also note that this has to be added in the same line as existing params, not in a new line.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sources:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/docker/for-linux/issues/1112#issuecomment-699512425\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/docker/for-linux/issues/1112#issuecomment-699512425</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://forums.raspberrypi.com//viewtopic.php?t=203128\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://forums.raspberrypi.com//viewtopic.php?t=203128</a></li>\n</ul>\n"
  } ],
